The paper proposes a novel approach for time series classification using fully convolutional networks augmented with LSTM RNN sub-modules. This approach involves deep learning techniques and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed models also involve image processing techniques, such as convolutional neural networks, which fall under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also explores the usage of attention mechanism, which is a popular technique in natural language processing (cs.CL) and has been recently applied to time series analysis. Additionally, the paper involves the usage of recurrent neural networks, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE).
